  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.14.0\n\n### What happened?\n\ncalling `debug_traceTransaction` with non-default tracer (e.g., `{\"tracer\": \"callTracer\"}`, cf. https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/developers/evm-tracing/built-in-tracers#config) ignores the tracer param and just runs `debug_traceTransaction` with the default tracer (`structLogs`), instead of failing more loudly (ex. with code `-36202`) as i would expect.\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n```bash\r\ncurl localhost:8545 -X POST   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"   --data '{\"method\": \"debug_traceTransaction\", \"params\": [\"<your favorite tx hash here>\", {\"tracer\": \"callTracer\", \"onlyTopCall\": true}],\"id\":1,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}' \r\n```\n\n### Search terms\n\ndebug_traceTransaction, trace, callTracer",
